From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0042/N] fdlibm.h: prefer __linux__ over _ALLBSD_SOURCE for endian.h

Same pattern as patch 0040 for UnixConstants.java.template.

`fdlibm.h` picks the endian header on `_ALLBSD_SOURCE` first:

  #ifdef _ALLBSD_SOURCE
  #include <machine/endian.h>
  #elif defined(__linux__)
  #define __USE_BSD 1
  #include <endian.h>
  #endif

For our cross-build, the BUILDJDK pass compiles
`libfdlibm/StrictMath.o` on the HOST (x86 Linux) where
`_ALLBSD_SOURCE` is set (by patches 0004 / 0037) and `__linux__`
is also set (by the host compiler). The BSD branch wins, but
glibc has no `<machine/endian.h>` — fatal error.

Reorder: prefer `__linux__` when both are defined, so the
BUILDJDK pass on Linux uses `<endian.h>`. The native target build
on CheriBSD will still hit the BSD branch.

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md §6 (patch 0042)

--- a/src/java.base/share/native/libfdlibm/fdlibm.h
+++ b/src/java.base/share/native/libfdlibm/fdlibm.h
@@ -24,9 +24,9 @@
  * questions.
  */

-#ifdef _ALLBSD_SOURCE
+#if defined(_ALLBSD_SOURCE) && !defined(__linux__)
 #include <machine/endian.h>
-#elif defined(__linux__)
+#elif defined(__linux__) || defined(__GLIBC__)
 #define __USE_BSD 1
 #include <endian.h>
 #endif
